abstract: PHILADELPHIA FOR five and two-thirds innings, Ken Forsch had shut the Phillies out with five hits. This was the  first game of the playoff for the National League pennant, the fourth such opportunity for the Phils in five years, their sixth postseason tournament since mankind came down out of the trees.

abstract: Joe Torre, who this season managed to get the Mets out of the National League's Eastern Division cellar, will be rehired to lead the team next season and perhaps beyond that, sources close to the Mets' front office said yesterday.

abstract: SAN DIEGO, Oct. 5--They're building a trolley line here, and the Navy won't be running it. To old-timers here, that is a sign that San Diego is changing.

abstract: Suffern, the Rockland County Public School Athletic League defender, beat Spring Valley, 27-0, yesterday. Spring Valley had lost 16 consecutive games before havine won its first two this season.

WATKINS GLEN, N.Y., Oct. 4-- Mario Andretti, who won the World Championship of Drivers in 1978 in a Lotus, says he has had it with the Britain-based team. As the 1980 Grand Prix season winds down to its finish here this weekend, Andretti has let it be known he will switch to another team next year.

abstract: WARETOWN WHEN Dorothea Dix Lawrence ventured into the Pine Barrens four decades ago in hot pursuit of re  search on folk music and culture, she came across a group called the Pinehawkers--Bill Britton playing the fiddle, Walt Britton on banjo and Maurice (Merce) Ridgway on guitar.
headline_main: The Voice of the Pine Barrens Still Rings Out

abstract: MONTREAL, Oct. 4--The great chase ended tonight in the National League's Eastern Division when the Philadelphia Phillies tied the Montreal Expos with two out in the ninth inning and then defeated them, 6-4, in the 11th on a home run by Mike Schmidt.
